<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge" />

    <!--Bootstrap-->
    <link
      href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.2.1/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
      integrity="sha384-GJzZqFGwb1QTTN6wy59ffF1BuGJpLSa9DkKMp0DgiMDm4iYMj70gZWKYbI706tWS"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/template.css" />
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/img/icon.png" type="image/png" />

    <!-- Add icon library -->
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css"
    />

    <!--reCaptcha Script-->
    <script src="https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js" async defer></script>

    <!-- Load Stripe.js on your website. -->
    <script src="https://js.stripe.com/v3"></script>

    <title><%= title %></title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <script>
      fbq('track', 'ViewContent', {
        value: 19.99,
        currency: 'CAD',
      });
    
      fbq('track', 'AddToCart', {
        value: 19.99,
        currency: 'CAD',
      });
  
      fbq('track', 'Purchase', {
        value: 19.99,
        currency: 'CAD',
      });
    </script>
      
    <!--Nav bar-->
    <% include templates/header.ejs %>

    <div class="container" style="padding-top:100px;">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
          <h4 class="display-4 mt-3 pt-5">
            Rootcase for iPhone X/XS - Coral Sand
          </h1>
          <p class="lead">
                A case that doesn't pollute our space. Learn 
                more below!
          </p>

          <form action="/charge" method="POST">
            <script
              src="https://checkout.stripe.com/checkout.js"
              class="stripe-button"
              data-key="<%= stripePublishableKey %>"
              data-amount="1999"
              data-name="iPhone X/Xs BioCase"
              data-description="A biodegradeable phone case"
              data-image="/img/marketplace.png"
              data-locale="auto"
              data-currency="cad"
              data-shippingAddress="true"
              data-billingAddress="true"
              data-zip-code="true"
            ></script>
            <script>
              // Hide default stripe button
              document.getElementsByClassName(
                'stripe-button-el'
              )[0].style.display = 'none';
            </script>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-lg">
              Purchase For $19.99 CAD
            </button>
          </form>
          <br />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <img src="/img/product.png" alt="" class="img-fluid" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
            <h5 class="display-4 mt-3 pt-5">Description:</h5>
            <p class="lead">
                Available for iPhone X/XS, Rootcase is an eco-friendly alternative
                to traditional plastic phone cases. 100% BPA-free and biodegradable,
                by purchasing Rootcase you’re also supporting a plastic-free future
                for the planet. Order today and get free shipping on all orders.
            </p>
              <p class="lead">
                The soft and easy to grip texture of Rootcase offers a secure and 
                comfortable feel in your hand. Due to the natural shock-absorbing 
                properties of wheat fibre, Rootcase also offers great protection from 
                drops and scratches.
              </p>
              <p class="lead">
                Coral sand is a naturally occurring type of sand that originates from the great 
                coral reefs of the world. It’s iconic smooth texture and rich colour are common 
                sights at tropical beaches across the globe. Grains of coral sand are produced naturally 
                when small pieces of coral are broken off by marine creatures big and small, and carried by the 
                currents around the planet. However, this incredible natural phenomenon is at risk at being lost 
                forever. Due to increased plastic pollution in the oceans, coral reefs have started to die off around the 
                world. Because of warmer water temperatures, some coral reefs have also begun to bleach, turning pale and 
                losing their rich colours. If this continues, it’s very possible that a future without the simple beauty of 
                coral sand will become a reality. 
              </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <% include templates/footer.ejs %>

    <!-- Optional JavaScript -->
    <!-- jQuery first, then Popper.js, then Bootstrap JS -->
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.1.0.js"></script>
    <script
      src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.14.6/umd/popper.min.js"
      integrity="sha384-wHAiFfRlMFy6i5SRaxvfOCifBUQy1xHdJ/yoi7FRNXMRBu5WHdZYu1hA6ZOblgut"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    ></script>
    <script
      src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.2.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"
      integrity="sha384-B0UglyR+jN6CkvvICOB2joaf5I4l3gm9GU6Hc1og6Ls7i6U/mkkaduKaBhlAXv9k"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    ></script>

    <script src="/js/index.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
